// CPU profiling by sampling: a perf_event program fires at 99 Hz on every CPU,
// captures the running stack, and aggregates it in-kernel. Basis of flame graphs.

// 1. Hot KERNEL stacks (which kernel paths burn CPU)
profile:hz:99 { @[kstack] = count(); }

// 2. Per-process samples (run separately): who is on-CPU
//    profile:hz:99 { @samples[comm] = count(); }
//    swapper/N samples = CPU N was idle.
